## üìÑ Working Papers

### Current Publications

1. **[Can Computers Be Emotionally Creative? Exploring The Iron Giant Theorem](papers/working-paper-emotional-creativity.md)** (2024)
   - Comprehensive exploration of affective computing foundations
   - Analysis of recent emotion AI research (2023-2024)
   - Computational models of cognitive dissonance and resonance
   - Aesthetic transfer mechanisms and MIDI-emotion research
   - Catharsis, emergence, and philosophical implications
   - Full APA-style citations and annotated references

**Abstract**: This paper examines whether computers can achieve emotional creativity by integrating recent advances in affective computing, multi-objective reinforcement learning, and aesthetic modeling. Drawing on emotion recognition research achieving 84% accuracy (Zhang et al., 2024) and multimodal understanding systems (Wang et al., 2024), we propose computational architectures capable of experiencing functional analogs to cognitive dissonance and resonance. The paper demonstrates that through systematic aesthetic training‚Äîparticularly using MIDI-emotion correlations‚ÄîAI agents can internalize frameworks for evaluating emotional effectiveness. We argue that agents creating to resolve measurable internal tensions exhibit functional emotional creativity, regardless of unresolvable questions about subjective experience.

### Coming Soon

